that I'm not old enough.

27:30.710 --> 27:32.951
"Can't do this. No, no, honey,
can't do this. You're too young--"

27:32.991 --> 27:35.310
Hold on, hold on.
Sit down.

27:37.071 --> 27:41.231
Look. Number one, you ain't too young.
You're a young woman.

27:41.270 --> 27:43.792
It's just that I could...
get in trouble.

27:43.871 --> 27:47.031
- Now, you don't want your daddy
to get in trouble, do you?
- No.

27:47.109 --> 27:50.831
I don't want you getting into any more
trouble. I know it wasn't your fault.

27:50.912 --> 27:53.431
I know you didn't mean it.

27:55.111 --> 27:58.631
You don't know what
that means to your daddy.

27:58.711 --> 28:01.191
Now, let's hit them Skittles.

28:01.271 --> 28:04.111
Your brother, he's doin'
all right, huh?

28:04.192 --> 28:06.032
- He is so good.
- Yeah?

28:06.112 --> 28:08.352
He is better than good, Daddy.
You should see him play.

28:08.432 --> 28:10.431
He's a zillion times better
than when you last saw him.

28:10.512 --> 28:13.592
- Remember when he used to be
so weak on his left hand?
- Yeah.

28:13.672 --> 28:15.911
Naw, now he can handle it
with both.

28:15.992 --> 28:18.273
- And he can shake so good.
- Can he?

28:18.353 --> 28:20.472
I bet he can finally beat you.

28:21.592 --> 28:22.832
You think so?

28:25.793 --> 28:28.353
-Yeah, he probably can.

28:30.792 --> 28:34.193
You've reached Mary and Jesus.
We're not at home.

28:34.274 --> 28:37.192
- Leave a message at the beep.

28:37.273 --> 28:39.353
It's me, baby. It's Lala.

28:44.993 --> 28:47.833
Hello, son.

28:47.872 --> 28:50.233
Mary, what did I tell you
about letting strangers in the house?

28:50.314 --> 28:53.632
- He's not a stranger. He's our father.
- I don't have a father.

28:53.673 --> 28:55.234
- Hey, wait a minute--
- Daddy, he's trippin'.

28:55.314 --> 28:58.193
Trippin'? We'll see who's trippin'
later on tonight.

28:58.274 --> 29:01.473
- What did I tell you about
talking to strangers anyway?
- "Don't do it."

29:01.514 --> 29:03.953
- And why?
- Because it may cause us harm.

29:04.034 --> 29:06.754
So why did you let
this stranger in our house?

29:06.834 --> 29:08.194
Mary, do you hear me talking to you?
Don't play deaf.

29:08.194 --> 29:08.434
Mary, do you hear me talking to you?
Don't play deaf.

29:08.514 --> 29:11.354
I'm not standing here for
my health, and you ain't deaf.

29:11.394 --> 29:14.514
- Don't talk to your sister like that.
- Am I talkin' to you?

29:14.594 --> 29:18.795
Matter of fact, I don't
even know why you're here.

29:18.874 --> 29:20.835
Mary, answer me right now.

29:20.875 --> 29:23.035
I won't do it again,
I promise!

29:23.116 --> 29:25.795
It's time for you
to get to steppin'.

29:25.835 --> 29:29.276
And I'd appreciate it if you don't
ever walk through that door ever again.

29:29.354 --> 29:31.995
All right.
Look, I need to talk to you.

29:32.035 --> 29:35.395
- Why?
- I just need to. When can we talk?

29:35.475 --> 29:37.715
I don't know.
I'm usually around.

29:37.796 --> 29:40.755
- Where you gonna be at?
'Cause this is kinda urgent.
- I'm usually at the Garden.

29:40.835 --> 29:42.676
- All right.
- All right.

29:42.756 --> 29:46.195
- I'll see you down there.
- Yeah, you can see me there.

29:51.036 --> 29:53.595
Enjoy the Skittles, baby.

29:53.676 --> 29:56.356
Now you enjoy walkin'
out that front door.

29:58.955 --> 30:01.114
- Where you think you're goin'?
- Help!

30:01.155 --> 30:03.195
Get in there!

30:06.317 --> 30:08.437
Open the door!

30:08.516 --> 30:11.357
- Who's tryin' to break the door down?
- Booger!

30:13.356 --> 30:16.156
What's up?

30:16.196 --> 30:19.236
Hey, how y'all doin'?

30:19.317 --> 30:22.517
- Not good.
- What's wrong, dear?

30:22.557 --> 30:25.037
- Guess who showed at the apartment?
- Who?

30:25.117 --> 30:27.438
- Daddy.
- Lord have mercy!

30:27.517 --> 30:30.196
- Booger, take your cousin in your room.
- Go in the room.

30:30.277 --> 30:32.277
Come on, Mary. Um--

30:32.358 --> 30:34.637
You can play with
my Sony Playstation.

30:34.677 --> 30:37.718
- Good, 'cause I can always beat you.
- I'm gettin' good at--

30:37.797 --> 30:39.878
Sit down, son.

30:41.077 --> 30:43.397
When did all this happen?

30:45.357 --> 30:48.958
- About half an hour ago.
- What did he say? What does he want?

30:48.998 --> 30:51.118
He says he wants to speak to me.
He says it's urgent.

30:51.197 --> 30:54.879
- It don't make no sense.
- It makes perfect sense.
He smells the money.

30:54.958 --> 30:59.158
What I'd like to know, how does a
convicted murderer get out so quick?

30:59.238 --> 31:02.679
How can this happen?
